<br>
There are always an abundance of ideas on how to help the Wizard in grouping situations.  There are 2 aspects which seem to nullify the suggestion.  1) They infringe on another classes abilities.  2) They impact the solo ability and/or raid value of the class.  With this in mind, I was thinking of how we might be able to use our current spells and abilities.<br>
<br>
Parameters:<br>
Minimal impact on Solo Ability<br>
Minimal impact on Raid Ability<br>
Stay within the current abilities of the class<br>
<br>
What hinders the wizard from reaching his full potential in group situations?  In my opinion, it is the fact that preventing damage is more important to the group than causing damage.  It is true that by causing quick damage, we are killing the target faster and therefore less damage is incurred.  However, if the mob is causing damage very fast, the healer is forced to use less efficient healing methods to keep up with the damage.  Many groups are limited by healer mana even when a mob is slowed; because of this back-up healers are often sought in experience group situations.<br>
<br>
The wizard is capable of preventing damage using our stun line of spells.  In the Kunark era, it was possible to chain stun mobs to help reduce the damage output.  When we stole agro, we could actually survive a round or 2 of melee.  In PoP the mobs hit too fast and too hard to dare to attempt this, the agro will almost surely get you killed.  <br>
<br>
If a wizard could chain stun without the extremely high agro that goes with stun, a wizard could effectively reduce the damage output of the mob.  Without stun agro however, there would be nothing to prevent multiple wizards from effectively chain stunning a mob and reducing the damage output to zero.  With that in mind, I would suggest a non-stacking debuff added to the 'wizard stun' effect.  This way it would not be possible to completely avoid damage, the mob would be able to melee in-between stuns.  <br>
<br>
With resists, the chain of stuns would perform like a variable slow.  The higher the level of wizard the more stuns they can add to chain.  Because our stun spells are not the most efficient, the wizard would be making a decision between causing damage and preventing damage.  Using multiple spells slots also limits the function of the wizard if he needs/chooses to perform this role.  A wizard would never replace a reliable slower, but in a pinch we might be able to supplement a lesser slow, or use the ability in ghetto type groups without key classes.  In testing, resist levels and agro modifiers could be adjusted to increase or decrease the level of effectiveness of this method.<br>
<br>
<br>
Deficits:<br>
Lower ability to help the group prevent damage.<br>
Agro limited more than mana limited. <br>
<br>
Spells:<br>
Telekin: 8 sec stun 18 sec recast 900 damage<br>
Marker's Discord: 8 sec stun 24 sec recast 750 damage<br>
Thunderbold: 3 sec stun 18 sec recast 600 damage<br>
Tishan's Discord: 5 sec stun 18 sec recast 260 damage<br>
<br>
Changes:<br>
Remove/significantly reduce stun portion of agro, if this is not possible add an offsetting amount of agro reduction.<br>
Increase level  affected target to 65<br>
Add non-overwritable debuff (similar to Manaburn) to prevent stun locking for balance<br>
<br>
Another thing that I miss is the ability to root an extra mob on incoming.  Yes, we can still do it, but again agro makes this a far too risky maneuver.  Some classes have agro radius reduction type spells, which aid the pulling of single mobs.  We need to deal with them after they are already at camp.  If the agro were reduced on Greater Fetter, we could better perform the crowd control function, and aid traditional crowd control by separating and keeping the mobs off of primary mezzer.<br>
<br>
Deficits:<br>
Rooting has such high agro that a quickly broken root or resist on incoming can = dead wizard.<br>
<br>
Spells:<br>
Greater Fetter<br>
<br>
Changes:<br>
Remove/significantly reduce agro, if this is not possible add an offsetting amount of agro reduction.<br>
<br>
Neither of these change would significantly impact our solo abilities positively.  By changing the stuns, it will take away the ability to stun lock mobs.  Because in solo environments we own all of the agro, adjusting agro has no affect.  The overwhelming majority of raid level mobs are unstunable, having little impact on our raiding ability.<br>
<br>
What do you think?  Workable?  Not significant enough to impact groupablity?  Overpowering?<br>
