<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I hate the holy trinity crap by the way, it's not like they're instantly snatched up for groups when they want one. Heh, Enchanters are losing their spots to Shaman fairly often too. - Rombus<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I agree that the 'holy trinity' is no longer true, it seems to me that now more than ever groups look for specific abilities over classes.  I do think certain classes spend more time looking for groups than others.  I have not seen Enchanters losing spots to Shaman, perhaps this happens more in the elemental planes.  If this is happening often, it goes to show you the power of slow and heal.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>We are balanced in xp groups, solo, and raids if not balanced we are well above the mark of the average class in each 3 fields. - Zuratuli<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I do not see evidence of our above average status in experience groups.  The damage charts and logs seem to support that we are on par in lower up time groups (in comparison to melee dps), and drop in damage as up time is more frequent or we are responsible snaring.  If we have a nuke item, it appears that a Wizard can compete favorably, but alas the higher end click items are not common enough.  We can not compete with charm dps, and Mage dph has traditionally been better in a higher uptime group even with traditional pets.  <br>
<br>
Again, I don't want to give the idea we are broken.  I, like many others, would just like us to see us be more wanted for experience groups.  I am not saying my suggestion is the answer.  I don't think public opinion is won or lost here.  While grouping, I would never suggest that I was anything less than nuclear fission in action.<br>
