<br>
I'll say this only for clarity: Wizards are comfortably and easily outdone by Mages in damage per second and damage per hour in groups below level 50.  Everything you point to that helps Wizards helps Mages also (foci, resists, etc) except crits, which amount to a whopping 10% gain in power at best.  That doesn't make up the gap in any way.  Thus, Wizards have to hope either there are no mages around (happens too often, sadly) or that people will want them for their L337 snaring skillz, an ability shared by 5 other classes.  This doesn't equal great grouping ability, so there's a problem below level 50, and always will be.<br>
<br>
However, seeing as this isn't going to change and there's no way in hell SOE will fix the problem, focus on your strengths.  Make friends, group with them.  Solo when you can't get a group, or play another character.  Be the best, most well-informed Wizard you can be.  Get your strategies and power down rock solid, make few if any mistakes, be on top of everything.  Be the eyes and ears of the party, you'll have more freedom than anyone but the Cleric to watch battle spam and adds.  You as a player have to make up the small gap that's there in grouping ability because your class design won't do it.  Get the best gear you can, avoid fancy flashy stuff and stick to what makes you better at wizardry: INT, Mana, Focus.  Keep your aggro under control, don't screw up with AE or adds, evac when its needed and always be ready to port people in your group around.  Be friendly, fun, intelligent, and capable.  Know as much as you can about the area and targets, know more than everyone else if you can - role play the &quot;wise one&quot; aspect of Wizards.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Take it from me, there is no human on the planet with more experience on this matter:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Bitching on Message Boards about problems and ways Wizards need fixing will make <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ZERO DIFFERENCE</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to the SOE about the class.  There was a time they wanted input and did some small things, but they're all but done with EQ anyway, if they do anything it will be only something to playtest EQ2.  Don't come here with constant screaming complaints about how your favorite solo fishing hole was nerfed and the world is ending.  Don't come here talking about how the class &quot;sucks&quot; or is &quot;broken&quot; because all that accomplishes is general mockery and the possibility of others thinking Wizards suck and treating you like it in the game.<br>
<br>
Make friends.  Be a good player.  Enjoy yourself, its a game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=903.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=903.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=903.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=903.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=903.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=903.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm60">Graffe Forum News<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">Genera